  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/nagaraja-sa-001",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — identification of dominant uncertain inputs driving wide QoI bounds",
    "description": "Sobol first-order and total-order indices computed over five uncertain inputs (elastic modulus E_Ti, yield strength sigma_y, post-yield hardening exponent n, rod diameter tolerance delta_d, screw insertion torque T_ins) for all three QoIs. Results show sigma_y accounts for 61% of yield force variance and T_ins accounts for 38% of stiffness variance; these two inputs are the primary drivers of the wide confidence intervals documented in the validation results. Post-yield hardening exponent n contributes 29% of variance in force-at-40mm. Geometric tolerance delta_d and elastic modulus E_Ti are secondary contributors (Sobol total index below 0.15 for all QoIs). These findings directly inform the low confidence scores reported for stiffness (0.62) and yield force (0.58) ValidationResults and are the basis for the residual risk offset accepted in the DecisionRecord."
  },
